@database 303tracker_keyboard_shortcuts.guide
@author "Jeroen Schellekens"
@font topaz.font 8
@wordwrap
@width 80
@index Index1

@node Main "Keyboard shortcuts guide"
This Guide covers all the keyboard shortcuts available in 303tracker.
Choose a group of keyboard shortcuts you want to know its function of...

@{" Single keyboard shortcuts " link Alkey1}     @{" Keys with Shift holded " link Alkey2}

@{" Keys with Control holded " link Alkey3}      @{" Keys with Alt holded " link Alkey4}

@{" Keys with Left Amiga holded " link Alkey5}   @{" Keys with Left Amiga+Shift holded " link Alkey6}

@{" Keys with Right Amiga holded " link Alkey7}  @{" Shortcuts for requesters & windows " link Alkey8}
@endnode

@node Quit01 "Quit keys"

@{b}Y@{ub} = Yes (exit program)
@{b}N@{ub} = No  (get back to program)

@{b}ESC@{ub} = close window and get back to program

@endnode

@node File01 "File requester keys"

Cursor up   = scroll through directory Up
Cursor down = scroll through directory Down

@{" neuk me " link neuk}

@endnode

@node Alkey1 "Keyboard shortcuts 1"
Single keyboard shortcuts (without pressing Shift/Alt or other keys)
--------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}Return@{ub}          - Play current note and move cursor 1 down
@{b}Space@{ub}           - Toggle edit on/off
@{b}Tab@{ub}             - Select next column to edit

@{b}Del@{ub}             - Kill current note and move cursor 1 down (If edit on)
@{b}Help@{ub}            - Online help (AmigaGuide)
@{b}Escape@{ub}          - Abort process (Cancel) or exit window
                         - Toggle edit on/off
@{b}Return@{ub}          - Confirm action (OK) and close window
                         - Preview current note
@{b}.@{ub}               - Toggle Edit-style (Draw, Line, or Zoomed)
@{b}Control@{ub}         - Locate mouse at selected position(column,note-position)

@{b}Cursor Up@{ub}       - Move cursor 1 up in note-column
@{b}Cursor Down@{ub}     - Move cursor 1 down in note-column

@{b}Cursor Left@{ub}     - Increase/transpose value with 10  (or 1 in Note Column)
@{b}Cursor Right@{ub}    - Decrease/transpose value with 10  (or 1 in Note Column)

Same as:

@{b}+@{ub}               - Increase/transpose value with 10  (or 1 in Note Column)
@{b}-@{ub}               - Decrease/transpose value with 10  (or 1 in Note Column)

@{b}F6@{ub}              - Set cursor at '00' in note-column
@{b}F7@{ub}              - Set cursor at '08' in note-column
@{b}F8@{ub}              - Set cursor at '16' in note-column
@{b}F9@{ub}              - Set cursor at '24' in note-column
@{b}F10@{ub}             - Set cursor at '31' in note-column

@{b}?@{ub}               - About

@endnode

@node Alkey2 "Keyboard shortcuts 2"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Shift holded
------------------------------------------------

@{b}Tab@{ub} + @{b}Shift@{ub}     - Select previous column to edit

@{b}CursUp@{ub}+@{b}Shift@{ub}    - Move cursor 4 up in note-column
@{b}CursDn@{ub}+@{b}Shift@{ub}    - Move cursor 4 down in note-column

@{b}CursLe@{ub}+@{b}Shift@{ub}    - Increase/transpose value with 100 (or 12 in Note Column)
@{b}CursRi@{ub}+@{b}Shift@{ub}    - Decrease/transpose value with 100 (or 12 in Note Column)

Same as:

@{b}+@{ub} + @{b}Shift@{ub}       - Increase/transpose value with 100 (or 12 in Note Column)
@{b}-@{ub} + @{b}Shift@{ub}       - Decrease/transpose value with 100 (or 12 in Note Column)

@{b}Shift@{ub} +

        @{b}F3@{ub}      - Cut selected column to buffer
        @{b}F4@{ub}      - Copy selected column to buffer
        @{b}F5@{ub}      - Paste buffer to selected column

@endnode

@node Alkey3 "Keyboard shortcuts 3"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Control holded
--------------------------------------------------

@{b}CursUp@{ub}+@{b}Ctrl@{ub}     - Move cursor 8 up in note-column AND holds at end
@{b}CursDn@{ub}+@{b}Ctrl@{ub}     - Move cursor 8 down in note-column AND holds at end

@endnode

@node Alkey4 "Keyboard shortcuts 4"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Alt holded (and evt. Shift)
---------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}Alt@{ub} +

        @{b}F3@{ub}      - Cut current pattern to buffer
        @{b}F4@{ub}      - Copy current pattern to buffer
        @{b}F5@{ub}      - Paste buffer to current pattern

        @{b}a@{ub}       - Audio channels active/inactive (allocate them)
        @{b}c@{ub}       - Midi Control settings
        @{b}e@{ub}       - Effects-Menu
        @{b}g@{ub}       - Goto Pattern n
        @{b}i@{ub}       - Goto Mixer window
        @{b}l@{ub}       - Length of Pattern
        @{b}m@{ub}       - Midi Port active/inactive
        @{b}n@{ub}       - Name Pattern
        @{b}o@{ub}       - Edit Envelopes of Pattern
        @{b}p@{ub}       - Play options
        @{b}r@{ub}       - Randomize Pattern
        @{b}s@{ub}       - Set shuffle amount
        @{b}v@{ub}       - VCO/VCF/VCA settings
        @{b}x@{ub}       - Goto the Arexx-Support Window

        @{b}->@{ub}      - Next Pattern
        @{b}<-@{ub}      - Previous Pattern

        @{b}t@{ub}       - Show Song/Pattern-information in titlebar

        @{b}Shift@{ub}   - Play Song

@endnode

@node Alkey5 "Keyboard shortcuts 5"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Left Amiga holded
-----------------------------------------------------

@{b}Left 'Amiga'@{ub} +

        @{b}Cursor Up@{ub} - Move mousepointer 6 pixels up
        @{b}Curs Down@{ub} - Move mousepointer 6 pixels down
        @{b}Curs Left@{ub} - Move mousepointer 8 pixels to left
        @{b}CursRight@{ub} - Move mousepointer 8 pixels to left

        @{b}F6@{ub}        - Set mousepointer at '00'
        @{b}F7@{ub}        - Set mousepointer at '08'
        @{b}F8@{ub}        - Set mousepointer at '16'
        @{b}F9@{ub}        - Set mousepointer at '24'
        @{b}F10@{ub}       - Set mousepointer at '31'

@endnode

@node Alkey6 "Keyboard shortcuts 6"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Left Amiga AND Shift holded
---------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}Left 'Amiga'@{ub} + @{b}Shift@{ub} +

        @{b}Cursor Up@{ub} - Move mousepointer 24 pixels up
        @{b}Curs Down@{ub} - Move mousepointer 24 pixels down
        @{b}Curs Left@{ub} - Move mousepointer 80 pixels to left
        @{b}CursRight@{ub} - Move mousepointer 80 pixels to left

@endnode

@node Alkey7 "Keyboard shortcuts 7"
Keyboard shortcuts combination with Right Amiga holded (and evt. Shift)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}Right 'Amiga'@{ub} +

        @{b}a@{ub}         - Mark entire pattern as range
        @{b}b@{ub}         - Mark range
        @{b}c@{ub}         - Copy selected range to buffer
        @{b}d@{ub}         -
        @{b}e@{ub}         - Arrange Song
        @{b}f@{ub}         - Render Quick
        @{b}g@{ub}         - Set grid
        @{b}h@{ub}         - Invert selected column Horizontal
        @{b}i@{ub}         - Song Info
        @{b}j@{ub}         - Shift Horizontal
        @{b}k@{ub}         - Shift Vertical
        @{b}l@{ub}         - Load sample
        @{b}m@{ub}         - Midi Sample Dump
        @{b}n@{ub}         - Name Song
        @{b}o@{ub}         - Load song
        @{b}p@{ub}         - Play sample (-window)
        @{b}q@{ub}         - Quit 303-tracker
        @{b}r@{ub}         - Goto render-menu
        @{b}s@{ub}         - Save rendered sample
        @{b}t@{ub}         - Transpose-menu
        @{b}u@{ub}         - Undo Last Action * NOT YET IMPLEMENTED *
        @{b}v@{ub}         - Paste buffer to current position
        @{b}w@{ub}         - Save song
        @{b}x@{ub}         - Cut selected range to buffer
        @{b}y@{ub}         - Invert selected column Vertical
        @{b}z@{ub}         - Randomize selected column

        @{b}Shift@{ub}     - Play Pattern

@endnode

@node Alkey8 "Keyboard shortcuts 8"
Other keyboard shortcuts available in 303tracker.
-------------------------------------------------

Requesters and Windows:

@{b}Escape@{ub}            - Abort process (Cancel) or exit/close a window
@{b}Return@{ub}            - Confirm action (OK) and close window

If the requester or window contains a button or more, the first letter of
the word printed in this button will be the keyboard shortcut for the
button. For example, if you want to quit, you'll get a requester wich asks
you if you are sure. Then you see two buttons, @{b}Yes@{ub} and @{b}No@{ub}. The keyboard
shortcut for @{b}Yes@{ub} is @{b}Y@{ub}, for @{b}No@{ub} press @{b}N@{ub}.


Online Help Window:

@{b}Cursor Up@{ub}         - Show previous page (if there is one)
@{b}Cursor Down@{ub}       - Show next page (if there is one)
@{b}Escape@{ub}            - Exit Help and get back to program

@endnode

@node Zone01 "Keyboard shortcut"
Keyboard options for editing notes
----------------------------------
@{b}Space@{ub} - Toggle Edit On/Off
@{b}Cursor Up & Down@{ub} - Move note-cursor up and down
@{b}Del@{ub} - Erase current note and move cursor 1 down

@{b}Z@{ub} - C-1/C-2    @{b}S@{ub} - C#1/C#2    @{b}Q@{ub} - C-2/C-3    @{b}2@{ub} - C#1/C#2
@{b}X@{ub} - D-1/D-2    @{b}D@{ub} - D#1/D#2    @{b}W@{ub} - D-2/D-3    @{b}3@{ub} - D#1/D#2
@{b}C@{ub} - E-1/E-2                   @{b}E@{ub} - E-2/E-3
@{b}V@{ub} - F-1/F-2    @{b}G@{ub} - F#1/F#2    @{b}R@{ub} - F-2/F-3    @{b}5@{ub} - F#1/F#2
@{b}B@{ub} - G-1/G-2    @{b}H@{ub} - G#1/G#2    @{b}T@{ub} - G-2/G-3    @{b}6@{ub} - G#1/G#2
@{b}N@{ub} - A-1/A-2    @{b}J@{ub} - A#1/A#2    @{b}Y@{ub} - A-2/A-3    @{b}7@{ub} - A#1/A#2
@{b}M@{ub} - B-1/B-2                   @{b}U@{ub} - B-2/B-3
@endnode

