Requesters and Windows:
-----------------------
@{b}Escape@{ub}            - Abort process (Cancel) or exit/close a window
@{b}Return@{ub}            - Confirm action (OK) and close window

If the requester or window contains a button or more, the first letter of
the word printed in this button will be the keyboard shortcut for the
button. For example, if you want to quit, you'll get a requester wich asks
you if you are sure. Then you see two buttons, @{b}Yes@{ub} and @{b}No@{ub}. The keyboard
shortcut for @{b}Yes@{ub} is @{b}Y@{ub}, for @{b}No@{ub} press @{b}N@{ub}.


Online Help Window:
-------------------
@{b}Cursor Up@{ub}         - Show previous page (if there is one)
@{b}Cursor Down@{ub}       - Show next page (if there is one)
@{b}Escape@{ub}            - Exit Help and get back to program

@endnode
